Prep the ingredients: Set the broiler to high or preheat the #oven{} to 500 degrees. Thinly slice the @garlic{4%cloves}(thinly sliced). Trim and discard the bottom inch from the @asparagus{12%oz}, then cut into 1-inch pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large oven-proof pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook, tossing for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the asparagus and cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until bright green. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @milk{8%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, ½ cup water, and @pesto{4%tbsp} to the pan and stir to combine. Add the @cheese tortelloni{18%oz} to the pan (don't worry if they aren't submerged). Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, for ~{6-8%minutes}, until the sauce becomes very thick and the tortellini are soft.

> TIP: If the sauce becomes too thick, simply add a splash of water to the pan.

While the tortellini simmers, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @parmesan cheese{2%oz}, and a large drizzle of olive oil in a #small bowl{}. Season the mixture with salt and pepper.

> HINT: if you don't have an oven-proof pan, transfer the tortellini to a #baking dish{} (ours is 9"x13").

Bake the tortellini gratin: Sprinkle the breadcrumb mixture over the tortellini. Transfer to the #oven{} to broil for ~{1-2%minutes}, until browned and bubbly.

Finish and plate: Divide the tortellini gratin between #bowls{} and dig in!